---- MODULE TwoPhase ----
plus/* MODULE Alternate */   /* This module specifies the two-phase handshake. The system is pictured as follows and represented actions are A_0 (Producer going first) or 	A _1(Consumer goes second).*/    INSTANCE FiniteSets LOCAL Naturals SPECIFICATION TPSpec   CONFIGURATION RM
/* Invariant: */     /* The invariant that is needed for the proof. Inv will be defined in a suitable refinement mapping (substitution 	for variable v).*/    INVARIANT_TPTypeOK      PRECONDITIONS A, B SPECIFICATION TPSpec   PROOFS SpecImplementsAlternateSpec
/* The following statement imports for every operator D of module Alternative a definition AD to equal the 	definition OF d with vBar substituted	for variables and xInit , XAct parameters. Thus AFASubst is defined as follows: */    DEFINITIONS A_D = {a, b} SPECIFICATION TPSpec   INVARIANT SpecImplementsAlternateSpec
/* The following theorem standard proof that one specification implements (the safety part of) another 	specification under a refinement mapping. In fact the temporal leaf proofs will be exactly same ones for every such Proofs, in realistic example non-temporal Leaf Proves are replaced by fairly long structured prooves--especially substeps numbered <2>: */    THEOREM SpecImplementsAlternateSpec => {A_D} (INVARIANT)
/* TLC Configuration :*/   CONFIGURATION Rm; /* The set of all valid indices for zero-indexed sequence s. ZIndices(s), the length 	of zseq, and a conversion from one index to another are defined as follows: */    INSTANCE Naturals SPECIFICATION TPSpec
/* Invariant :*/   /* The invariant that is needed for proof Inv will be used in refinement mapping (substitution of variable v). 	vBar, and substituted parameters xInit , XAct are defined as follows: */    INVARIANT_TPTypeOK SPECIFICATION TPSpec
/* Substituting a state function Vbar for the variables.*/   /* The following statement imports from module Alternate all operator D of 	moduleAlternative, definition AD to equal Definition OF d with vBar substituted	for variable and xInit , XAct parameters in this case: */    DEFINITIONS A_D = {a', b'} SPECIFICATION TPSpec   INVARIANT SpecImplementsTpSpec
